   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="description">
      <p> Habitat </p>
      <p> Largely montane, in woods which are wet and/or have deep litter. In <tp:taxon-name> Fagus
         </tp:taxon-name> woodland in Wales . </p>
   </tp:treatment-sec>
   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p> Remarks </p>
      <p> Telfer et al. (2015) discussed whether this species is native or introduced to the UK .
         Five subspecies have been described from the Pyrenees and the Montagne Noire in France ,
         but only <tp:taxon-name> C. amoena ssp. confusa </tp:taxon-name> has been found outside
         France : in Belgium and Wales ( Telfer et al. 2015 ). </p>
